# Who Wired This - Input & UI Rules

## Input Source of Truth
- `PlayerInputBridge` is the primary source of gameplay intent state
- For gameplay actions, prefer reading through `PlayerInputBridge` first
- Legacy `UnityEngine.Input` checks are fallback paths; do not expand fallback usage unless needed for compatibility

## Pointer/UI Guardrails
- Preserve pointer-over-UI protection for click-based interactions:
  - Check `EventSystem.current != null`
  - Use `EventSystem.current.IsPointerOverGameObject()`
- Mouse/pointer interactions should not fire world interactions when pointer is over UI

## HUD and Panels
- `HUDController` owns top-bar and panel toggles (`ToggleInventory`, `ToggleHelp`, `ToggleMenuPanel`)
- `MessagePanel` owns popup/confirmation behavior
- New UI behavior should integrate through these existing controllers before adding new panel managers

## UI Binding Conventions
- Use null-safe listener setup for optional inspector refs (`button?.onClick.AddListener(...)`)
- Keep display refresh logic isolated in dedicated methods (`RefreshScore`, `RefreshTimer`, etc.)
- Prefer one-way manager-to-UI updates via events, not polling

## Restart/Scene Behavior
- Restart currently reloads active scene name through `SceneManager.LoadScene(activeScene.name)`
- Any new reset behavior should keep manager/UI state consistent with scene reload flow
